[$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)] M2 DONE: Walked the public-root chunks that hit every page. Findings:

  03vharm7a1~9r.js (55 KB / 13 KB gz) — Next.js next/headers + next/dynamic-tracking. Framework, can't prune.
  0p0p6yfobvglb.js (36 KB /  9.7 KB gz) — sonner Toaster (rendered in app/layout.tsx) + MembershipsProvider.
  0-2umy1z-gdzs.js (36 KB / 10.5 KB gz) — next-auth/react SessionProvider + GoogleTranslateLoader stub.
  0--o4905mhw.e.js (44 KB /  9.3 KB gz) — Next.js dynamic tracking / async-local-storage. Framework.
  01252jp0ai4yh.js (28 KB /  8.8 KB gz) — react-server-dom-webpack client. Framework.
  0ayull263if0p.js (32 KB /  9.0 KB gz) — Next router / cache-key creation. Framework.

  ONLY user-controllable target: sonner's <Toaster /> is mounted at root layout
  but is invisible until a toast() call. Same lazy-load pattern as v1.80.8 modals.

  Verified NOT actionable:
  - polyfill-nomodule.js: served via <script nomodule>, modern browsers skip
    download entirely. Browserslist (Chrome93+, Safari16+) means 100% of
    visitors skip. Next.js doesn't expose a config to disable.
  - core-js usage: the polyfill bundle ships from Next.js itself, not from
    any of our deps (no `core-js` directory in node_modules).
  - lucide-react: 28 callsites use named imports of specific icons (1.x is
    per-icon files). Already tree-shaken.
  - Prisma in client bundle: zero @prisma/* references in .next/static/chunks
    (v1.80.7 fix held).

[$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)] M3 DONE: One low-risk fix: extract <Toaster> into a 'use client' wrapper that uses next/dynamic to lazy-load sonner. Pattern matches v1.80.8 modal lazy-load. Expected savings: sonner's ~36 KB raw / ~10 KB gz moves out of root chunk on every public page; pages that import { toast } from 'sonner' directly (CopyMatchdayLink, AssignPlayerClient) still pull sonner but only on that route, in a per-route chunk.

M4 DONE: Applied — extracted ToasterMount.tsx (use client + next/dynamic + ssr:false) and replaced static Toaster import in app/layout.tsx. Post-fix build passes. tsc clean. 2738 unit tests pass + 3 new regression-target tests in perfPhase4d.test.ts pass. Stash-pop verified — re-injecting <Toaster> into layout.tsx fails 2 of the 3 new tests.

